Prompt Level: Law [SEP] Prompt: Rewrite the termination section of the contract to take into account possible discrimination either against or by the employer or employee. Compare your amendment with the model. This is a non-graded activity. [SEP] Response: Termination of Employment

7.1. Following the successful completion of the probationary period described in paragraph 4, Party A may terminate the employment of Party B at any time:

(a) for just cause at common law, without advance notice or compensation;

(b) without just cause, provided Party A gives Party B advance written notice or compensation in lieu of notice equal to one month plus two weeks per year of completed service, up to a maximum of fifteen (15) months;

(c) provided that no termination shall be carried out on grounds of discrimination against Party B based on race, gender, age, religion, disability, sexual orientation, or any other protected characteristic under applicable law;

(d) if Party B believes that termination is due to discrimination, Party B has the right to raise a grievance or pursue legal action without prejudice.

7.2. Party B may terminate employment by providing Party A at least eight (8) weeks’ advance written notice of resignation.

7.3. Party B must also ensure that the decision to resign is free from discriminatory pressure or harassment by Party A.

7.4. Both parties agree to comply fully with all anti-discrimination laws and policies throughout the term of employment and during termination proceedings.

